Backpack Recycler  UO Outlands

Full automation script to identify, recycle, and organize your backpack after farming. It handles the entire post-farm cleanup loop on its own.

What the script does, in order:

Item identification  auto-equips the Glasses of Identification, identifies every "unidentified" weapon and armor in your backpack, then puts the glasses back. Wands, lockpicks, trap tools, bandages, vet supplies, pouches, and potions are ignored during this phase.
Unidentified pre-scan  before opening the sewing kit, it scans the backpack for items with "unidentified" in their description. If none are found, the entire recycling phase is skipped, so the kit isn't opened for nothing.
Sewing Kit recycling  opens the sewing kit and auto-recycles low-quality weapons and armor based on a smart preservation logic (detailed below).
Junk movement  moves junk (common gems, excess regs, configurable trash) to a JunkBag, while keeping in your backpack everything useful: bandages, veterinary supplies, lockpicks, trap removal tools, trap tools, pouches, potions, wands, sewing kit, and tools in general.
Outlands new weapon support  recognizes by name: dual wield rapier, duel wield katana, dual wield norse axe/sabre/scimitar/tracker knife, francisca, chakram, hurlbat, javelin, throwing knife, throwing star.
Preservation logic (what is kept vs. recycled):

Always kept (no condition):
Weapon damage tier: power, vanquishing / vanquish
Any slaying / slayer weapon (beastial, daemonic, elemental, undead, humanoid, monstrous, nature, construct, etc.)
Region slayers: kraul, ossuary, aegis, inferno, petram, mausoleum, darkmire, wilderness, shadowspire, netherzone, time dungeon, nusero, pulma, ocean, tidal, cavernam
aspect, training, activated, and unidentified items (never destroyed)
Blessed items (full block  never moved, never recycled)
Kept by configurable flags (all enabled by default):
Armor: invulnerability, fortification
Weapon damage: supremely / exceedingly / eminently potent
Weapon accuracy: supremely / exceedingly / eminently accurate
Instruments: supremely / exceedingly / eminently melodious
You can turn any of these off by setting the corresponding keep_* flag at the top to 0.
Conditionally kept (only if paired with another modifier):
might and force weapons are only kept when they also carry another relevant property (durable / invulnerability / vanquishing / slayer / region slayer / etc.). A bare might/force with no companion mod is treated as junk and recycled.
accurate, potent, melodious, and surpassingly tiers are only kept when the item already has a companion mod that justified keeping it.
Force-recycled (always destroyed regardless of mods):
Low-tier armor shells: leather bustier, female studded chest, ringmail skirt, all chainmail pieces (chain coif/tunic/leggings/mail)
Generic shields (only heater shield, chaos shield, and order shield are kept; the rest are recycled)
Never touched (stays in backpack, never moved or recycled):
Bandages, veterinary supplies, lockpicks, trap removal tools, trap tools, pouches, potions, wands, sewing kit, and configured tools.
How to use:

Paste the script into your Razor client.
Have in your backpack: Sewing Kit and Glasses of Identification.
Have a JunkBag (a secondary bag/container) inside your backpack to receive junk. The script will prompt you to target the JunkBag on first run.
(Optional) Adjust the keep_* flags at the top of the script to choose what to preserve. 1 = keep, 0 = recycle.
(Optional) Tweak the wait values at the top if your connection is slower:
moveWaitMs  delay between item moves
bagOpenWaitMs  delay when opening a bag
recycleWaitMs  delay between recycles
worldSaveWaitMs  pause during world save
Run the script after farming. It identifies ’ recycles ’ organizes on its own and stops when done.
Note: If there are no unidentified items in your backpack, the sewing kit isn't even opened, saving time and clicks.